description:
When cycleState.inProgressIds is non-empty, each crashed task is reset with a separate Haiku dispatch in a for loop: N tasks = N sequential agents.

Fix: merge into one dispatchShell:
  if (cycleState.inProgressIds.length > 0) {
    await dispatchShell(
      cycleState.inProgressIds.map(id => `bd update ${id} --status=open`),
      { model: MODEL_HAIKU, label: 'reset-orphans', phase: 'Plan' }
    );
  }

Sequencing note (cross-talk with 4lj): cycleState.inProgressIds comes from checkCycleState which runs inside 4ljs parallel(). This dispatchShell must always start AFTER parallel() resolves -- never inside it.

Acceptance criteria:
- All in-progress resets dispatched as a single dispatchShell
- dispatchShell starts only after parallel(sprint-meta, checkCycleState) resolves
- Behaviour identical to the loop for 1, 2, and N tasks
- maxTurns set to inProgressIds.length + 1

In the Harvest phase (~line 1576-1600), calibration-update (commits calibration.json locally, no push) and close-sprint-goals (bd close <ids>, no push) run sequentially. Both must complete before beads-export-cleanup (which exports final state and pushes). Zero data dependency between the two.

Fix:
  await parallel([
    () => dispatch(calibrationUpdatePrompt, { label: 'calibration-update' }),
    () => dispatch(closeSprintGoalsPrompt,  { label: 'close-sprint-goals' }),
  ]);
  await dispatch(beadsExportCleanupPrompt, { label: 'beads-export-cleanup' });

Acceptance criteria:
- calibration-update and close-sprint-goals dispatch simultaneously
- beads-export-cleanup still runs after both complete
